:: chp1-leave-letter [dream] 
The cat snuggles up beside you meowing softly. Such a cuddle monster! You feel really tired. 
You walk towards the bed and decide that a quick cat nap is okay. Besides, the cat fully agrees with this by jumping up
onto the bed.

You can see the cats mouthing moving but don't hear any meowing. It sort of sounds like "don't close your eyes". But
that can't be. Can cats really talk? 

[[Ask politely what was said?|chp1-ask-cat]]


:: chp1-ask-cat [dream]
'' ADD E ART showing cat talking''

Samson looks at you in disbelief with a tilted head. "I was trying to tell you not to close your eyes. Midnight Moon
will steal your dreams. Dreamland needs you. Please open the letter!"

Is this a dream? Sometimes it is hard to know. You sort of remember having dinner, going to the park and that bath that
was too cold. 

"Listen, there is not much time." says the cat licking the right paw. "Open the letter when you see it next."

You try to stop your eyes from closing. This is really kool listening to a talking cat. You give up, the bed is to cozy
and warm. You close your eyes and everything goes dark.

You wake up with the long shadows of the sun coming through the window. The evening star is out and the birds have gone
to bed.

[[Continue|chp1-left-letter-wake-up]]


:: chp1-left-letter-wake-up [awake]
With a big stretch, you open your eyes. The wall clock says it's 7:30am. The curtains cover the window. The cat is
snuggled up at the bottom of the bed. You remember having some kind of dream but it's blurry.

You roll out of bed, get dressed and go about your Saturday. The weathers warm and most of your friends will be at thr
beach today! 

After a wonderfull BBQ with your family and a hot bath. You get dressed into your favorite pj's and snuggle into bed.
The cat jumps up and claims the end of the bed. Both of you drift off to sleep as the moon glows through your window.

[[Contine|Start]]


:: chp1-open-letter [dream]
You walk over to the coffee table. Looking down at the letter it is wrapped very [[oddly|chp1-describe-letter-envelop]]. You just
want to open it up but something causes you to pause. Turning around, there is the cat wwatching you very closely.
Those large green eyes staring straight through you. Well, you [[could stare back|chp1-stare-at-cat]] but you're not
sure that is really neccessary.

You trying sounding out one of the words but it doesn't sound like any word you know. So, it's the web to the rescue. 
Running downstairs you grab your moms phone and snap a picture. A couple of clicks and the photo is off to Google. 
Hopefully the all knowing Google will be able to tell you what language it is. Even better is it will tell you what
''it'' says. What seems like forever, okay only a few seconds pass. The phone beeps. Why does mom have the beep bloop
beep ringer. Maybe you'll change it later to something kooler. There is an answer on the screen, //French// is the
language. Google could only figure out a single phrase:''magic magnifing glass needed''. Maybe by next week Google will
learn how to read old hand writing. But you can not wait that long!

You pick up the enevlope again, turning it over slowly. You really want to open the letter now. So you rip open the letter
and look inside. [[Take out the piece of paper|chp1-take-out-letter]] or perhaps ask the internet what a [[magic magnifying
glass is|chp1-magic-magnifying-glass]].


:: chp1-magic-magnifying-glass [dream] 
A //magic magnifying glass// is a fairy tale item used by Alice in Wonderland. See page 237 of the book.

You grab the book off of your shelf (mom has been reading it to you at night). Quickly you flip to the page. There is
Alice holding a magnifying glass. Ok so Google got that right. But how does that help me?

[[Contine|chp1-take-out-letter]]


:: chp1-stare-at-cat [dream]
''ADD E ART showing the cat''

Sometimes that cat spookys you. At Halloween that is totally fun but not right now. Those large green eyes that never
seem to blink. You should know, you have battled so many times in the past to see who could win at staring. No
suprise the cat always wins.

You figure it will make you feel better if you stare anyway. With a squint and making a silly face you start at
Samson. A small grin runs emerges, the challenge is accepted!

You want to blink so bad, but a win feels so close now. Just a few more seconds. The window rattles and distracts
Samson. The cat jumps down and walks towards the window. The next seconds the cat is looking out the window with the
tail flickering from side to side. 

So, does that mean you win? Just as you're about to bask in your glory but the cat looks back at you with a grin.

[[Contine|chp1-open-letter]]


:: chp1-take-out-letter [dream]
The letter is a single piece of yellowish paper. Some of the words are smudged. Looking closer, the words look like
those on the outside of the envelope, //French//. There is no way Google will understand these you sigh. 

You look at the bottom of the letter, there is something written in pencil. You start to read it....

//Find the magic magnifying glass in your dreams.//

You're not sure what to think. This is a strange riddle and everyone knows you like riddles. Did mom do this? 

Well, better write this down so you don't forget in your journal. 

[[Continue|chp1-leaving-the-dream]]


:: chp1-describe-letter-envelop [dream]
''ADD E ART showing outside of letter''

Where is this even from? You've on;y ever seen white envelops and brown packages come in the mail.

Oh well, it doesn't matter. The evenlope paer is brown with stains. It feels very thick. String is wrapped around it.
You notice the two large stamps are not in English. Both of them contain an image of the Effel Tower.

[[Lets open and see what's inside|chp1-open-letter]] 


:: chp1-leaving-the-dream [dream]
As you look at the stamps on the letter, the images start to move. You begin to see glimpses of a forest with a large
balloon sailing above it. Next, the moon appears but it looks very different than how you remember it. The last image is
water in a well. The stamps look like they did as you rub your eyes. What is happening? 

But before you can think any longer, the color in the room starts to fade. You can not see the wall anymore. Oh no, you
are ''waking up''.

[[Contine|chp1-waking-up-first-time]]


:: chp1-waking-up-first-time [awake letter]
'' ADD E ART OF ROOM''

The light is bright in the room as you open your eyes.

You look at the coffee table, but there is no letter on it. The cat is curled up at the bottom of the bed.

That was strange you think. Through it was a really nice dream. Something catches your eyes, your trusty journal is
lying on the floor. That's not where you out it.

You jump out of bed, grab it and open it to the last page. There is a picture of a letter with the words //magic
magnifying glass//, //the cat talks but only in dreams//.

[[Tell mom|chp1-tell-mom]]
[[Talk to the cat|chp1-talk-to-cat]]


:: chp1-tell-mom [awake]
Mom listens and smiles. When you are done telling her your dream and what you found in the journal, she laughs and says
she didn't write in your journal. You ask her if cats can talk? She gives you a big hug and says that would be really
great if they could, but no they can not.

The puzzle is growing. The more you think about and the clues in your journal the more you're sure someone is trying to
tell you something important. 

But what and why?

[[#link]]


:: chp1-write-first-letter-ideas-journal [dream]
''ADD E ART picture of journal''

You have so many questions but the first is what's wrong with Google? Maybe you'll ask mom to help write an email about
this. In the meantime you, want to write down a few ideas so you don't forget them.

You write down //magic magnifying glass// and //the cat talks but only in dreams//. That should be enough to help you
remember.

"If mom saw you chewing on the end of the pencil she would be mad with you" said the cat. You jump and look arond for
the voice. "I`m at your feet" laughs the cat.

"There is much I need to tell you but..." as the cats tail starts to puff up. "Dreamland is in trouble, the letter has
chosen you to help. Please, please say yes." pleads the cat.

You're not sure what to make of this. But a talking cat, this is the best!

"Please listen" meowed the cat. "I can only talk to you when you dream. Everything we talk about or you see will
disappear when you wake up."
"But perhaps, just perhaps, writing them down in your journal will survive. I certainly hope so".

You catch yourself staring at the cat. How rude. So many questions to ask but which ones? 

[[Ask the cat why he can talk.|chp1-why-can-cat-talk]]
[[What is Dreamland?|chp1-dreamland-back-story]]
[[Why would I forget?|chp1-why-things-in-dreams-disappear]]
